ce:section.ce:para:
Through facile hydrothermal treatment of biomass waste at 200 °C for 8 h, highly fluorescent biomass CQDs were synthesized (Scheme 1
                        ). In order to study the morphology, phase and surface groups of CQDs, various characterizations were carried out. Fig. 1
                        a showed the TEM image of the MF-CQDs. The prepared MF-CQDs was almost spherical and monodisperse in water without obvious reunion. As shown in Fig. 1b, a high resolution TEM (HRTEM) image taken from a particle point showed a distinct lattice spacing of 0.21 nm, which was correspond to the lattice spacing (100) of the graphene structure [32,33]. Based on statistical analysis of more than 170 particles, these CQDs showed size distribution between 1.32 and 4.87 nm, with an average size of 2.60 nm (inset of Fig. 1a). The XRD patterns of all obtained CQDs (Fig. S2) exhibited a wide diffraction peak at around 23 degrees owing to their small size or partial graphitization. This result was similar to the previously reported CQDs [33–35].
